Ministry of Economy and Public Finances was the historical name of the current Ministry of the Treasury and the Ministry of Finance. It was concerned with finance and monetary matters, and its position within the Government of Argentina was analogous to the finance ministers of some countries (e.g. the United States Treasury Secretary). The Ministers currently in charge of its duties are members of the President's Cabinet, the posts are held by Nicol√°s Dujovne as the Minister of the Treasury and Luis Caputo as the Minister of Finance.
